<exercise checkit-seed="0002" checkit-slug="P1" checkit-title="Sample Spaces">
    <statement>
        <p>
Suppose you have 3 spinners that have 5, 2, and 3 equally sized spaces, respectively. Write out the sample space that corresponds to this situation. What is the probability that the sum of the spinner results is more than 7?
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
        The sample space is
        </p>
        <me>
\begin{array} {llllll} \{(1,1,1), &amp; (1,1,2), &amp; (1,1,3), &amp; (1,2,1), &amp; (1,2,2), &amp; (1,2,3), \\ (2,1,1), &amp; (2,1,2), &amp; (2,1,3), &amp; (2,2,1), &amp; (2,2,2), &amp; (2,2,3), \\ (3,1,1), &amp; (3,1,2), &amp; (3,1,3), &amp; (3,2,1), &amp; (3,2,2), &amp; (3,2,3), \\ (4,1,1), &amp; (4,1,2), &amp; (4,1,3), &amp; (4,2,1), &amp; (4,2,2), &amp; (4,2,3), \\ (5,1,1), &amp; (5,1,2), &amp; (5,1,3), &amp; (5,2,1), &amp; (5,2,2), &amp; (5,2,3) \}\end{array}
        </me>
        <p>
        The probability is 9/30.
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
